- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the reverse engineering of a circuit function and proposes a method to recover the correct gate-level schematic.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with gate-level schematics and their reverse engineering.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses SAT-based techniques which are often used in machine learning.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the use of fault injection and probing to recover gate-level schematics, which could be related to programming languages.
